Module courseplanner
Package courseplanner

Class Planner

  • java.lang.Object
    • courseplanner.Planner
  • public class Planner
extends java.lang.Object
    The Planner class implements an abstract data type for a list of courses and some common operations on such lists.
    Author:
    Sayan Sivakumaran e-mail: sayan.sivakumaran@stonybrook.edu Stony Brook ID: 110261379

      • addCourse

        public void addCourse​(Course course,
                      int position)
               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                      FullPlannerException,
                      NegativeNumberException
        Adds a new course at the specified position.
        Parameters:
        course - The new course to be added.
        position - The position (preference) of this course on the list.
        Preconditions:
        This Course object has been instantiated and 1 ≤ position ≤ (courseCount + 1). The number of Course objects in this Planner is less than MAX_COURSES.
        Postconditions:
        The new Course is now listed in the correct preference on the list. All Courses that originally had position greater than or equal to position are moved back one position.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Indicates that position is not within the valid range.
        FullPlannerException - Indicates that there is no more room in the Planner for an additional course.
        NegativeNumberException - Indicates that either the code or section passed in is negative.

      • addCourse

        public void addCourse​(Course course)
               throws FullPlannerException,
                      NegativeNumberException
        Adds a new course at the end of the list.
        Parameters:
        course - The new course to be added.
        Preconditions:
        The Course object has been instantiated and the number of Course objects in this Planner is less than MAX_COURSES.
        Postconditions:
        The new Course is now listed at the end of the list.
        Throws:
        FullPlannerException - Indicates that there is no more room in the Planner for an additional course.
        NegativeNumberException - Indicates that either the code or section passed in is negative.

      • removeCourse

        public void removeCourse​(int position)
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Removes a course at the specified position.
        Parameters:
        position - the position in the Planner where the Course will be removed from
        Preconditions:
        This Planner has been instantiated and 1 ≤ position ≤ (courseCount).
        Postconditions:
        The Course at the desired position has been removed. All Courses that originally had position greater than or equal to position are moved backward one position.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Indicates that position is not within the valid range.
